- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is likely because the paper deals with power control and interference management in a wireless network context.
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is likely because the paper mentions a Stackelberg game to model the interaction between primary and secondary transmitters with conflicting objectives.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is likely because the paper discusses power control policies and their impact on the system performance.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with signal processing and transmission in a wireless communication context.
